.TH WJ 1 "2026" "wj 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wj \- cross-project daily task & time tracker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wj
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ args ]
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wj
tracks what you work on across every project from one command line. Each
action appends to an immutable per-day TSV event log; status tables, the
schedule grid, the multi-day gantt, reports and exports are all
.I derived
by replaying that log, so your data stays plain, greppable and easy to analyse.
.PP
The project is auto-detected from the git remote, falling back to the repository
folder name, then to
.IR default_project .
Run with no command to show today's status (or launch the UI when
.I interface
is set to
.IR ui ).
.SH TASK COMMANDS
.TP
.BI "start " "desc | P#"
Begin a new task; it gets the next id (T1, T2, ... per day). Runs alongside any
task already going in the same project; pass
.B --auto-pause
(or set
.B auto_pause=on
in the config) to pause that task first. Given a pending id (P#) it promotes that
backlog item instead, carrying its description and project.
.TP
.BI "continue " "id " "\fB--date\fR " date
Pick up a past day's task today: copies that task's description, project, and tags
into a fresh task for today (a new id, with its own clock) and appends a note
recording the lineage (\fIcontinued from <date> <id>\fR). The
.B --date
source day is required; the new task is always written to today. Use
.B --at
to set its start time and
.B --project
to override the carried-over project. The original task is left untouched.
.TP
.BI "pause " "[id] [why]"
Pause the running task (or the given id). Stops its clock.
.TP
.BI "resume " [id]
Resume the most-recent paused/deferred task (or the given id). Runs in parallel
by default;
.B --auto-pause
pauses the project's other running task first.
.TP
.BI "complete " [id]
Finish a task and sum its tracked time.
.TP
.BI "defer " "[id] [why]"
Set a task aside (blocked, or to pick up another day).
.TP
.BI "log " note
Attach a timestamped note to the running task.
.TP
.BI "amend " "[id] desc"
Replace a task's description (running task, or given id). Appends an event;
never rewrites history.
.TP
.BI "move " "[id] proj"
Re-home a task to another project (fix wrong auto-detection).
.TP
.BI "tag " "<id> <tag...>"
Add one or more free-form labels to a task \(em a cross-cutting axis beside its
project. Tags are normalized (lowercased; a leading '#' and spaces stripped, so
"High Priority" becomes high-priority). They are matched by
.B search
and aggregated by
.BR "report --by tag" .
.TP
.BI "untag " "<id> <tag...>"
Remove one or more labels from a task.
.TP
.BI "cancel " [id]
Void a mistaken task: 0 time, hidden from status/grid/report (kept in the raw
log for audit).
.TP
.B undo
Take back the last logged event on a day (today, or
.BR --date )
by dropping the log's last line. Repeat to walk further back. Because
.B continue
writes two events, undoing a carry-over takes two passes.
.PP
The state changes are idempotent: repeating one whose target state the task
already holds \(em
.B pause
on a paused task,
.B resume
on a running one,
.B complete
on a completed one, and so on \(em appends nothing to the log and just prints,
e.g.,
.IR "T1  already paused" .
.SH VIEW & ANALYSIS
.TP
.B ls
List currently-open tasks. Today by default;
.B --days N
scans the last N days.
.TP
.BI "show " id
Full timeline of one task. Today by default;
.B --date
for a past day.
.TP
.BI "status " [date]
Per-task totals table for a day (default: today). The default command.
.TP
.BI "grid " [date]
Slot-by-slot schedule for a day. The time axis is framed by
.IR shift_start / shift_end ,
auto-expanding to include any work tracked outside those hours (and auto-fitting
the day when the bounds are unset), so nothing is ever clipped.
.TP
.B gantt
Multi-day overview: rows (\fB--by\fR project|task) by days of tracked time.
Default range: the last 7 days through \fB--to\fR.
.TP
.B report
Aggregate time across a date range, grouped by \fB--by\fR.
.TP
.B export
Dump raw events as csv / json / tsv over a date range.
.TP
.BI "search " query
Find tasks across all recorded days by a case-insensitive substring of the id,
project, or description. Most-recent first.
.PP
The read views
.RB ( status ", " show ", " grid ", " gantt ", " search ", " pending )
also accept
.B --json
for a stable machine-readable contract \(em this is what the UI front-end consumes.
.SH PENDING (BACKLOG)
Tasks you have not started yet live in a separate backlog (ids P1, P2, ...,
stored in \fIpending.tsv\fR). They stay out of the time views until promoted
with \fBstart \fIP#\fR.
.TP
.BI "add " desc
Add a backlog task.
.B --project
sets its project;
.B --due
a deadline.
.TP
.B pending
List the backlog in manual (pinned) order.
.TP
.BI "due " "P# date|-"
Set, or clear (\fB-\fR), a pending task's deadline.
.TP
.BI "raise " P#
Move a pending task one step up.
.TP
.BI "lower " P#
Move a pending task one step down.
.TP
.BI "drop " P#
Remove a pending task without starting it.
.TP
.BI "assign " "P# who"
Hand a backlog item to a teammate: it moves to their list (becoming
.IR who/P# ).
You act only on your own items; assign one to yourself to pick it up. Shared
journals also accept
.B pending --mine
to list only your backlog. Items are author-partitioned like the day log, so the
backlog merges conflict-free.
.SH SYNC (SHARED JOURNAL)
Turn the data directory into a shared, multi-author journal over git. Each author
writes their own per-day file (DD.<actor>.tsv), so concurrent work never
conflicts; a union merge driver handles the same-author-two-machines case.
Authorship is the
.I actor
config (default: your git email, then $USER).
.TP
.BI "sync init " url
Make the data dir a git repo, install the union merge rule, stamp your author on
existing day files, wire up the remote, and do the first push/pull. Run once per
machine.
.TP
.B sync
Commit local changes, pull (rebase), then push. Reads afterwards show everyone's
tasks \(em yours as bare
.IR T# ,
teammates' as
.IR actor/T# .
Non-interactive callers (e.g. the wj-tui front-end) never block on an ssh
passphrase: keep your key in an agent, or sync manually from a shell.
.TP
.B sync status
Branch, clean/uncommitted, and ahead/behind counts.
.TP
.B team
Who is working on what right now across every author in the shared log: each
author's currently-running task (or idle) and their tracked total for the day
(today, or
.BR --date ).
See also
.B report --by person
for range rollups by author.
.SH OTHER
.TP
.B ui
Launch the wj-tui front-end (requires the
.B wj-tui
binary). A bare
.B wj
launches it too when
.I interface=ui
in the config.
.TP
.B config
Print the path to the active config file.
.TP
.BI "completion " SHELL
Print a completion script:
.B completion bash
or
.BR "completion zsh" .
.TP
.B version
Print the wj version (also \fB--version\fR, \fB-V\fR).
.TP
.B help
Show the built-in help.
.SH FLAGS
.TP
.BI "--at " TIME
Act at a past time instead of now. Flexible format: 9, 930, 0930, 9:30, 9.30,
9am, 9pm, 9:30pm all normalise to HH:MM.
.TP
.BI "--date " YYYY-MM-DD
Act on another day (alias \fB--on\fR). Combine with \fB--at\fR to reconstruct a
past day; defaults the day for status/grid.
.TP
.BI "--days " N
ls: how many days back to scan. Default 1 (today).
.TP
.BI "--project " NAME
Override project detection (e.g. for non-git work).
.TP
.BI "--from " D ", --to " D
Inclusive date range YYYY-MM-DD (report, export, gantt).
.TP
.BI "--by " KEY
Grouping: project | task | day | tag | person (report); project | task (gantt).
With
.BR "--by tag" ", a task is counted under each of its tags, so the report TOTAL"
can exceed real tracked time;
.B --by person
groups by author in a shared log.
.TP
.BI "--format " FMT
export format: csv | json | tsv. Default csv.
.TP
.BI "--due " YYYY-MM-DD
Optional deadline for a pending task (add).
.TP
.B --json
Emit a machine-readable view (status, show, grid, gantt, search, pending).
.TP
.B --parallel
start/resume: leave any other running task in the same project running (track
several in parallel). Overrides the
.B auto_pause
config for one command.
.TP
.B --auto-pause
start/resume: auto-pause the project's other running task first (one in-progress
task per project). Overrides the
.B auto_pause
config for one command.
.SH CONCURRENCY
By default tasks run in parallel: starting or resuming a task leaves any other
running task untouched
.RB ( auto_pause=off ).
Set
.B auto_pause=on
\(em or pass
.B --auto-pause
\(em to keep one in-progress task per project (start/resume auto-pauses the
previous one);
.B --parallel
forces the opposite for a single command. Different projects always run at once,
each its own grid column.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Config lives at
.I ~/.config/wj/cfg
(seeded on first run): a small INI file with
.RB [ tracking ], " [" ui ] " and " [ colors ]
sections of
.I key = value
lines, parsed (not executed). A legacy
.I ~/.config/wj/config
from an older version is migrated automatically (kept as
.IR config.bak ).
Keys:
.IR shift_start ", " shift_end " (default grid frame; comment out to auto-fit the grid to each day), "
.I slot_minutes
(grid step),
.I round
(down|nearest),
.I totals
(exact|slot),
.I default_project ", "
.I interface
(minimal|ui \(em the front-end for a bare
.BR wj ),
.I auto_pause
(on|off \(em start/resume auto-pause another running task in the same project;
default off),
.I accent
(the wj-tui border/header color \(em a 256-color code, #hex, or ANSI name; default 141, a purple),
.I layout
(the wj-tui panel arrangement \(em balanced|spotlight|golden|custom, default balanced; Shift+L cycles them live, z zooms the focused panel),
.I sidebar
(which side the wj-tui lists column sits on \(em left|right, default left),
.I confirm
(the wj-tui y/n guard before an action \(em all|destructive|off; default
destructive, which guards only cancel/void and pending drop),
.I icons
(the wj-tui status markers \(em on uses Nerd-Font icons and needs a patched font,
off uses the universal ASCII set; default off),
.IR layout_sidebar ", " layout_split
(optional overrides defining a
.I custom
layout \(em the sidebar width percent and the panel weights focused,hi,lo, e.g. 28 and 60,25,15),
and
.IR color_projects ", " color_tasks ", " color_pending ", " color_range ", " color_day ", " color_timeline
(the wj-tui per-panel title colors, one for each panel; same value formats as
.IR accent ).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/wj/cfg
Settings, INI format (override with \fB$WJ_CONFIG\fR).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/wj/YYYY/MM/DD.tsv
The append-only event log (override with \fB$WJ_DATA_DIR\fR).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.nf
wj start "Refactor auth" --project backend
wj log "extracted token service"
wj start "Code review" --project backend          # runs alongside the refactor
wj start "Standup" --project backend --auto-pause  # pause the others first
wj pause
wj resume
wj complete
wj status
wj gantt --from 2026-06-01 --to 2026-06-07 --by project
wj export --format csv > june.csv
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation and the optional terminal UI:
.UR https://github.com/Katestheimeno/wj
